B.MB=new A.dl("Warm & Passionate",B.a4V,"Warm oranges and reds stimulate appetite and social engagement \u2014 restaurants use this extensively. These wavelengths increase perceived temperature and urgency. The golden yellow tertiary adds optimism, creating a sunrise-to-sunset emotional arc.","Analogous","Orange, red, and yellow occupy adjacent warm positions, building intensity like heat rising.","Food and lifestyle content, social gatherings, event promotion, and any feature that wants to feel celebratory.","Dark brown text on seashell white meets AAA. Orange on white needs darkening for body text \u2014 pure orange fails AA below 18px.","Impossible to feel cold \u2014 the palette radiates physical warmth and social energy. Makes food photography look irresistible.","Red-orange palette triggers anxiety in some users. Extended exposure causes warm-hue fatigue. Poor for conveying calm or professionalism.")
B.a5n=s(["Warmth","Comfort","Harmony"],t.s)
B.Ms=new A.dl("Warm & Inviting",B.a5n,"Coral (Pantone 2019 Colour of the Year) bridges pink warmth and orange energy. Paired with sage green, it creates a Mediterranean harmony. The muted mustard accent adds earthiness, grounding the otherwise buoyant palette.","Complementary (Muted)","Coral and sage sit opposite each other but are desaturated enough to feel harmonious rather than clashing.","Lifestyle content, casual social discovery, home and garden marketplace, food photography backgrounds.","Warm dark text on blush white meets AAA. Coral on white passes AA at heading sizes but needs care at small text.","Feels like a Tuscan villa \u2014 warm stone, green shutters, terracotta pots. Universally pleasant and photogenic.","The muted quality can feel wishy-washy compared to bolder palettes. Navy tertiary feels out of place in the warm scheme.")
B.a4S=s(["Nostalgia","Warmth","Authenticity"],t.s)
B.MA=new A.dl("Warm & Nostalgic",B.a4S,'Gold and amber trigger memories of late afternoon sunlight \u2014 the "golden hour" beloved by photographers. These tones increase perceived warmth and sincerity. The teal accent provides a cool counterpoint like evening sky meeting warm earth.',"Complementary","Warm gold and cool teal form a natural complement \u2014 like sunset light against a blue sky.","Photo-centric feeds, nostalgic content, artisanal marketplace, and profiles emphasising authenticity and craft.","Dark earth text on warm cream meets AAA. Gold accents on white need darkening \u2014 pure gold fails AA for body text.","Every photo looks better in golden light \u2014 this palette acts as a built-in Instagram filter for the entire UI.","The warm tint can look yellowed on poorly calibrated screens. Teal accent feels disconnected from the golden warmth.")
B.a4x=s(["Heritage","Warmth","Groundedness"],t.s)
B.Ml=new A.dl("Earthy & Timeless",B.a4x,"Desert earth tones are among the oldest colours in human art \u2014 cave paintings used these exact pigments 40,000 years ago. Brown and ochre create deep comfort associations tied to wood, soil, and natural shelter. The palette feels ancestrally familiar.","Analogous (Earth)","Sand, terracotta, ochre, and umber form a naturally occurring palette \u2014 these colours literally sit together in sedimentary rock.","Artisan marketplaces, heritage content, travel and exploration, and profiles emphasising depth over flash.","Dark brown text on warm cream exceeds AAA. Earth-tone accents need darker values for small text \u2014 mid-browns can drift below AA.","Timeless and universally warm. The palette photographs beautifully and makes handmade items look premium.","Can read as old-fashioned to younger audiences expecting digital-native colours. Lacks any cool accent to create visual surprise.")
B.a5e=s(["Trust","Calm","Depth"],t.s)
B.Mv=new A.dl("Deep & Trustworthy",B.a5e,"Blue is the most universally preferred colour \u2014 57% of men and 35% of women cite it as their favourite. Deep ocean blues activate associations with stability, intelligence, and reliability. The graduating blues mimic water depth, creating a natural visual hierarchy.","Monochromatic","Multiple blues at different lightness values create depth and hierarchy without introducing competing hues.","Trust-critical interfaces \u2014 financial features, verified profiles, professional networking, and community safety messaging.","Dark navy text on alice blue meets AAA. Mid-blues on white need careful sizing \u2014 check AA compliance at body text sizes.","Universally inoffensive yet distinctive \u2014 ocean blues feel premium and trustworthy. The monochromatic approach makes hierarchy intuitive.","All-blue can feel corporate or cold for dating and social contexts. Lacks a warm accent to create emotional connection.")
B.a4g=s(["Clarity","Calm","Sophistication"],t.s)
B.Mq=new A.dl("Crisp & Serene",B.a4g,"The Nordic colour palette draws from Scandinavian winters \u2014 ice blues and cool grays that activate cooling associations. Studies show rooms in light blue tones are perceived as 3-4 degrees cooler. The muted saturation creates a sense of refined restraint and quiet confidence.","Analogous (Cool)","Steel blue, slate, and ice cyan sit adjacent on the cool side of the wheel, creating a cohesive Nordic atmosphere with subtle depth.","Clean data displays, professional profiles, content that benefits from a sense of measured calm and quiet authority.","Dark slate text on near-white exceeds AAA. Mid-tone blues on light backgrounds need careful checking \u2014 some fail AA at body sizes.","Distinctively Nordic \u2014 the muted palette feels intelligent and considered. Every element reads as intentionally placed.","Can feel cold or emotionally distant for dating and social warmth. The grey undertones may read as dull on low-quality screens.")
B.a57=s(["Romance","Gentleness","Elegance"],t.s)
B.Mw=new A.dl("Soft & Romantic",B.a57,"Pink tones lower aggression and create nurturing associations. Research shows exposure to pink reduces hostile behaviour (Baker-Miller pink). The mauve secondary adds sophistication, preventing the palette from feeling juvenile. Deep rose tertiary grounds the softness.","Analogous","Pink, mauve, and rose form a natural gradient through the cool-warm spectrum, unified by their red undertones.","Dating profiles, romantic content, beauty and wellness, and any context where softness and approachability are key.","Dark plum text on rose-white meets AAA. Pink accents on white are subtle \u2014 ensure interactive elements are large enough.","Genuinely romantic without being saccharine \u2014 the mauve-rose range adds maturity. Photos of people look great against these tones.","Strong gender association may deter some users. Can feel one-note without a contrasting accent. Fades on low-quality displays.")
B.a4w=s(["Growth","Balance","Renewal"],t.s)
B.Mt=new A.dl("Fresh & Balanced",B.a4w,"Green is processed by the largest number of retinal cones, making it the easiest colour to see. Forest greens trigger biophilic responses \u2014 studies show viewing green for 40 seconds improves creative performance by 20%. This palette mimics dappled sunlight through leaves.","Monochromatic","Dark to light greens create a natural gradient that reads like forest depth \u2014 dense canopy to bright clearing.","Wellness features, eco-conscious marketplace, outdoor activity social, and sustainability-focused content.","Dark green text on mint-white meets AAA. Mid-greens on white can drift below AA \u2014 use the darkest green for readable text.","Instantly signals health and nature. The darkest green feels premium, the lightest feels fresh \u2014 the range carries real emotional variation.","All-green interfaces can feel clinical or institutional. Lacks warmth for personal and dating contexts. Red-green colour blindness reduces differentiation for ~8% of men.")
B.a5a=s(["Stability","Neutrality","Timelessness"],t.s)
B.Mn=new A.dl("Neutral & Professional",B.a5a,"Cool grays with a blue-steel undertone signal competence and reliability. Grey amplifies surrounding content rather than competing with it. The blue accent provides a precise focal point that stands out sharply against the neutral background, like a single spotlight in a grey room.","Achromatic + Accent","Blue-grey scale provides structure through value alone, while the blue accent creates hierarchy without colour noise.","Content-first interfaces, photography showcases, professional profiles, and any context where content should do the talking.","Near-black on slate-white exceeds AAA. Mid-greys need careful management \u2014 the 4.5:1 AA threshold falls around the 50% mark.","The ultimate content showcase \u2014 nothing distracts from the user's photos, text, and listings. Feels timeless and permanent.","Minimal personality \u2014 the palette expresses little about the brand. Can feel dull in social contexts. Interactive elements need the blue accent to be distinguishable.")
B.a4L=s(["Mystery","Creativity","Intensity"],t.s)
B.Mu=new A.dl("Dark & Creative",B.a4L,"Purple on dark backgrounds is associated with creativity, luxury, and the mystical. Near-black reduces visual noise to zero, making purple accents feel precious \u2014 like gemstones in a dark room. The violet-to-lilac range stimulates creative and contemplative pathways.","Analogous (Dark)","Deep violet, purple, and lilac are neighbours on the cool side, creating a cohesive dark mood with enough variation to distinguish UI elements.","Night-mode interfaces, creative portfolios, music and entertainment feeds, premium dating experiences.","Lavender text on near-black meets AAA easily. Purple accents need sufficient lightness \u2014 dark purple on dark backgrounds disappears.","Dramatic and immersive \u2014 content floating on darkness feels curated and exclusive. Purple glows carry genuine visual magic.","Very dark interfaces lack visual landmarks for navigation. Extended use can feel heavy and isolating. True blacks cause OLED smearing.")
B.a47=s(["Adrenaline","Rebellion","Futurism"],t.s)
B.MD=new A.dl("Electric & Intense",B.a47,"Hot pink, electric teal, and neon yellow on near-black mirror the sensory overload of Tokyo nightlife signage. This combination triggers maximum alertness \u2014 the brain processes neon colours as urgent signals. The multi-chromatic approach creates a toxic-energy cocktail that feels dangerously exciting.","Tetradic (High Saturation)","Four fully-saturated hues form a rectangle on the colour wheel \u2014 maximum variety, maximum energy, minimal subtlety.","Gaming-adjacent social features, nightlife discovery, high-energy video feeds, youth and counter-culture audiences.","Neon pink on black has excellent contrast (14:1+). Teal on black is also strong. Yellow accents pop but need size care for readability.","Unmistakable and unforgettable \u2014 like a neon sign in a dark alley. Maximum attention-grabbing power for scroll-heavy feeds.","Visual assault in extended use. Impossible to use for body text at small sizes. Alienates older demographics immediately.")
B.a4A=s(["Innovation","Confidence","Dynamism"],t.s)
B.Mr=new A.dl("Bold & Futuristic",B.a4A,"Indigo-violet paired with electric cyan creates a digital-native palette that signals cutting-edge technology. Violet activates creative neural pathways while cyan adds clarity and focus. The pink tertiary prevents the cool palette from feeling sterile, adding an unexpected warmth that humanises the technology.","Split-Complementary (Dark)","Violet primary flanked by cyan and pink \u2014 warm and cool accents splitting the complement for dynamic tension without clash.","Tech-forward features, creative tools, music and media feeds, and audiences who identify with digital culture and innovation.","Light lavender text on deep navy-violet meets AAA. Cyan accents provide excellent visibility against the dark surface. Pink highlights read clearly at heading sizes.","The palette feels like the future \u2014 a digital aurora borealis. Each accent colour pops with its own personality against the dark canvas, creating genuine visual excitement.","The multi-chromatic dark palette can feel chaotic if overused. Needs careful restraint \u2014 too many competing neon accents create visual noise rather than hierarchy.")
B.a56=s([B.MB,B.Ms,B.MA,B.Ml,B.Mv,B.Mq,B.Mw,B.Mt,B.Mn,B.Mu,B.MD,B.Mr],t.hV)
